phrase
Element


phrase
&phrase.purpose;


&phrase.synopsis.gen;
Description



The Phrase element in DocBook has no specific semantic.
It is provided as a wrapper around a selection of words smaller than a
paragraph so that it is possible to provide an ID or other attributes for them.




For example, if you are making note of changes to a document using one
of the effectivity attributes, you might use Phrase to 
mark up specific sentences with revisions.


